@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Sustenance Allowance to Differently Abled Children";
    Layout = "~/Views/Shared/_LayoutMain.cshtml";
}
<div class="container py-4 bg-white">
    <div class="row mb-4">
        <div class="col-12 text-center pagetitlethree">
            <h1 class="display-4 fw-bold">Sustenance Allowance to Differently Abled Children</h1>
        </div>
    </div>
    <section class="mb-5">
        <div class="card border-0 shadow-sm">
            <div class="card-body">
                <h2 class="h4 fw-bold text-primary border-bottom pb-2">
                    <i class="bi bi-info-circle me-2"></i>Overview of the Scheme
                </h2>
                <div class="mt-3">
                    <p>1. With effect from 01 Jun 2023, Board of Governors has approved to establish a corpus fund in order to give a sustenance allowance of ₹ 12,000/- per month to a differently abled child whose Army parent dies while in service. As per the scheme details, the eligible child should be suffering from autistic spectrum disorders, cerebral palsy, mental retardation or a combination of any two or more of the following disabilities:</p>

                    <ul class="list-group list-group-flush ms-4 mb-3">
                        <li class="list-group-item d-flex border-0 ps-0">
                            <span class="fw-bold me-2">(a)</span>
                            <div>Blindness.</div>
                        </li>
                        <li class="list-group-item d-flex border-0 ps-0">
                            <span class="fw-bold me-2">(b)</span>
                            <div>Low Vision.</div>
                        </li>
                        <li class="list-group-item d-flex border-0 ps-0">
                            <span class="fw-bold me-2">(c)</span>
                            <div>Leprosy-cured.</div>
                        </li>
                        <li class="list-group-item d-flex border-0 ps-0">
                            <span class="fw-bold me-2">(d)</span>
                            <div>Hearing Impairment.</div>
                        </li>
                        <li class="list-group-item d-flex border-0 ps-0">
                            <span class="fw-bold me-2">(e)</span>
                            <div>Locomotor Disability.</div>
                        </li>
                        <li class="list-group-item d-flex border-0 ps-0">
                            <span class="fw-bold me-2">(f)</span>
                            <div>Mental illness.</div>
                        </li>
                    </ul>

                    <p>2. <strong>The other eligibility conditions are:</strong></p>

                    <ul class="list-group list-group-flush ms-4 mb-3">
                        <li class="list-group-item d-flex border-0 ps-0">
                            <span class="fw-bold me-2">(a)</span>
                            <div>The extent of disability must not be less than 40 per cent of any disability as certified by a medical authority.</div>
                        </li>
                        <li class="list-group-item d-flex border-0 ps-0">
                            <span class="fw-bold me-2">(b)</span>
                            <div>The child must be unable to earn a living.</div>
                        </li>
                        <li class="list-group-item d-flex border-0 ps-0">
                            <span class="fw-bold me-2">(c)</span>
                            <div>The disability of the child should manifest itself before the death of the service personnel while in service.</div>
                        </li>
                        <li class="list-group-item d-flex border-0 ps-0">
                            <span class="fw-bold me-2">(d)</span>
                            <div>The parent of the handicapped child should have died while on active service.</div>
                        </li>
                        <li class="list-group-item d-flex border-0 ps-0">
                            <span class="fw-bold me-2">(e)</span>
                            <div>The following cases will not be eligible:</div>
                        </li>
                    </ul>

                    <ul class="list-group list-group-flush ms-5 mb-3">
                        <li class="list-group-item d-flex border-0 ps-0">
                            <span class="fw-bold me-2">(i)</span>
                            <div>Handicapped children of serving members who have died prior to the scheme coming into effect.</div>
                        </li>
                        <li class="list-group-item d-flex border-0 ps-0">
                            <span class="fw-bold me-2">(ii)</span>
                            <div>Retired personnel who have died leaving behind handicapped children.</div>
                        </li>
                        <li class="list-group-item d-flex border-0 ps-0">
                            <span class="fw-bold me-2">(iii)</span>
                            <div>Handicapped children of all serving and retired personnel.</div>
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-5">
        <div class="card border-0 shadow-sm">
            <div class="card-body">
                <h2 class="h4 fw-bold text-primary border-bottom pb-2">
                    <i class="bi bi-clipboard-check me-2"></i>Updated Scheme Details
                </h2>
                <div class="mt-3">
                    <p>3. The sustenance allowance is given only to those children whose parent had died while in service on or after 27 Oct 2007 and is not applicable if the parent's death had occurred prior to 27 Oct 2007. In case the differently abled child dies subsequently, the payment would be continued to next severely handicapped child who meets the above conditions of the deceased soldier, if any. If no such child is there, the payment would be stopped by AGIF from the following month in which the child dies. The money will be remitted to the child through the guardian if he or she were a minor.</p>

                    <p>4. The Board of Governors of AGIF during its 78th meeting held on 19 Apr 2023 has reviewed the Sustenance Allowance existing Scheme. Monthly payment per child under the existing Sustenance Allowance Scheme has been increased from ₹ 6,000/- to ₹ 12,000/- per child. The scheme is now extended up to two differently abled children of AGIF Members who have died in harness wef 27 Oct 2011. Disability percentage and all other terms and conditions as applicable to the first child are applicable to the second child also. The existing beneficiaries will get the sustenance allowance on the revised rate wef 01 Jun 2023. There is no change to other terms and conditions for grant of sustenance allowance as specified vide AGIF letter No A/56271/R/AG/Ins (Coord) dated 26 Dec 2007.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-5">
        <div class="card border-info">
            <div class="card-header bg-info text-white">
                <h3 class="mb-0">Required Documents</h3>
            </div>
            <div class="card-body">
                <p>5. Documents required for obtaining sustenance allowance are as follows:</p>

                <ul class="list-group list-group-flush">
                    <li class="list-group-item d-flex">
                        <span class="fw-bold me-2">(a)</span>
                        <div>
                            Application for claiming allowance as per Appx 'A' to AGIF letter No A/56271/R/AGI/Ins (Coord) dt 26 Dec 2007
                            [<a href="../_forms/Sustenance_Allce_letter_dt_26_Dec_2007.pdf" target="_blank">Click Here To Get Army Order File</a>]
                        </div>
                    </li>
                    <li class="list-group-item d-flex">
                        <span class="fw-bold me-2">(b)</span>
                        <div>Life certificate as per Appx 'B' to AGIF letter No A/56271/R/AG/Ins (Coord) dt 26 Dec 2007.</div>
                    </li>
                    <li class="list-group-item d-flex">
                        <span class="fw-bold me-2">(c)</span>
                        <div>Non-earning cert as per Appx 'C' to AGIF letter No A/56271/R/AG/Ins (Coord) dt 26 Dec 2007.</div>
                    </li>
                    <li class="list-group-item d-flex">
                        <span class="fw-bold me-2">(d)</span>
                        <div>A medical certificate duly indicating the percentage of disability be issued from any nearest Military Hospital. The medical board must be constituted with at least three Medical Officers of which one shall be of the rank of Colonel and at least one shall be a specialist in the particular disability.</div>
                    </li>
                    <li class="list-group-item d-flex">
                        <span class="fw-bold me-2">(e)</span>
                        <div>Part II Order of birth of child (Kindred Roll portion att) former service.</div>
                    </li>
                    <li class="list-group-item d-flex">
                        <span class="fw-bold me-2">(f)</span>
                        <div>Part II Order for disability child (Kindred Roll portion att).</div>
                    </li>
                    <li class="list-group-item d-flex">
                        <span class="fw-bold me-2">(g)</span>
                        <div>Part II Order of death of serving soldier.</div>
                    </li>
                    <li class="list-group-item d-flex">
                        <span class="fw-bold me-2">(h)</span>
                        <div>Joint Bank details of Natural/legal guardian alongwith cancelled cheque or First Page of Bank Pass Book (not applicable for NDG).</div>
                    </li>
                    <li class="list-group-item d-flex">
                        <span class="fw-bold me-2">(j)</span>
                        <div>Cert from CO, parent unit in case Pt II order for different abled child pub after death of his father.</div>
                    </li>
                    <li class="list-group-item d-flex">
                        <span class="fw-bold me-2">(k)</span>
                        <div>PAN Card & Aadhar Card duly linked.</div>
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>
</div>